        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=6687&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=raiding%2Dnecros"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> well just about every week we have a "few" topics about what could be done to fix our class, and the same things are always said.  I personally feel there isnt much to do to fix our class, besides DoT stacking, and I wanna know how other necros look at this.</P><P>DoT stacking-  Of course if we got this fixed, we wouldnt be complaining for a long time :)  (well who in the hell am I kidding there will always be some of us who complain..).  The only problem I see with this is that they would have to re-write the whole engine coding, so I'm guessing this will only be possible in PoP?  If thats the case, most likely we will wind up being what rogues were to velious-- everyone will have a twink necro on their account.</P><P>Lifeburn-  As life burn is currently set up, it cant crit.  Maybe VI could change the skill around so instead of doing a 6 tick, 1500pt heal, it just does a 1500pt life tap?  This would give it the ability to crit, make it a little less dangerous to use it (i'm guessing youd still get low hp agro) and would make it so necros have a fun AA to go for :)  I know this wouldnt "fix" us, but it would help a ton.</P><P>No clue what to call this so this is the name!-  A huge part of high end battles is having enough DPS to go through the mobs health-regen, and do enough dmg to actually lower the mobs health.  Maybe its possible for necros to get a line of spells that lowers the mobs health-regen? say at level 54 we get a spell that does a 25% decrease,  and at 60 we get a 50% decrease?  No clue how VI would look at this, but just shooting out ideas really.</P><P><BR>Sorry for beating a dead horse, and I doubt this post actually makes sense at all, just trying to get a few more ideas out there-- if not new ideas I still like to think about how nice it would be to have DoT stacking..</P><P>~Maelie the Warlock<BR>WWW.SILENTRESURGENCE.ORG<BR></font></td>

