        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Dot stacking fixes the class, not necessarily balances us.  Adding in crit dots or some sort of casting dot fury and allowing the clarity line to stack with our lich line would go along ways towards balancing us properly.  Add in a cold dot line (similar to our fire line), a high level poison dd and a ST upgrade and a splurt upgrade and i'd be one happy camper. </P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Maybe VI could change the skill around so instead of doing a 6 tick, 1500pt heal, it just does a 1500pt life tap <hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>I really like this idea.  As it stands now, the risk doesnt justify the reward (dmg) that lifeburn provides.  By replacing the dot wiht a dd/tap, we'd reduce the risk, thus properly adjusting the AA.  In addition, changing it to a DD fixes the stacking issues and the does not hold issues with lifeburn.</P><P> <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Maybe its possible for necros to get a line of spells that lowers the mobs health-regen?  <hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote></P><P>This would be a sick spell line to get and something that would skyrocket necro demand in end game encounters and in raiding guilds.  I would drool over this one if ever implemented.  Potentially overpowering and something that could trivialize encounters, but regardless a great idea.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55675" target="_blank">Tencor Laureate - 60th Warlock</a><br><BR><a href="http://www.veilofsilence.org" target="_blank">Veil of Silence</a><br> <BR>Innoruuk Server<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
