         I think the idea of a regen reducer is a great idea. But topping it out at 10% would seem more practical and less potentially unbalancing.</P><P>To the people that say our disease based spells don't stop regen I have to say that I don't agree with you. From my own experience I have noted many many many times that when I lay a scourge or plague on a mob it tends to die much faster than the innate damage the spell causes would explain.</P><P>I have also noted many times that when I am diseased **MY** regen stops dead in it's tracks. I am strongly inclined to think that disease does in fact have an effect on a mob's regen.</P><P>Please note that since I'm not a VI programmer I don't state "it does" or "it does not" as many posters here are prone to doing. I merely state my opinion from long personal experience.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
